Story Summary (Plain English)

Sometimes the Equifax phone-verification service is slow or fails (timeout, error, or no response).
When that happens, IPS Web used to:

• crash with errors
• keep retrying the same request forever
• fill up server logs and disk space

This fix makes sure that when Equifax fails even once, the system:

• stops immediately
• returns a clean FAIL result
• does NOT retry in a loop
• does NOT crash

⸻

What Was Wrong Before

• Equifax timeout or error caused the system to break
• A null response caused a NullPointerException
• The workflow restarted the same phone verification again and again
• Logs grew endlessly (GBs per user)

⸻

What Is Fixed Now

• Equifax errors are handled safely
• Null responses are treated as failures
• Only one attempt is made per workflow
• The system returns FAIL and moves on
• No infinite loops
• No log flooding

⸻

Acceptance Criteria (Simple)

The fix is correct only if ALL of the following are true:
	1.	If Equifax times out, the system returns FAIL (no crash)
	2.	If Equifax returns null/empty response, the system returns FAIL
	3.	If Equifax returns an error (500), the system returns FAIL
	4.	The system does not retry repeatedly for the same user
	5.	Logs contain one error, not thousands
	6.	Normal successful Equifax calls still PASS

⸻

